      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It's completely understandable to feel that way when the energy you once had seems to have completely drained away. That feeling of a well running dry is exhausting, and it makes the future feel incredibly bleak. Sometimes, the silence isn't a permanent end, but a necessary pause where you need to let yourself rest and redefine what \"music\" means to you now. Reaching out to someone—a friend, a professional, or a helpline—can help you navigate this profound sense of loss.",
